     <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <h2><strong><span style="font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;">Introduction</span></strong></h2>
      <p><span style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;">This Privacy Policy (&ldquo;Policy&rdquo;) describes how Fire and Chill Wellness, LLC d/b/a Fire &amp; Chill and its subsidiaries and affiliates (collectively, &ldquo;Fire &amp; Chill&rdquo;, &ldquo;we&rdquo;, &ldquo;us&rdquo;, or &ldquo;our&rdquo;) collect, use, store, and share your information when (1) you access and/or use our websites, mobile applications, or other digital properties we own and operate, including&nbsp;</span><a href="https://www.firechill.com/"><u><span style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;">www.firechill.com</span></u></a><span style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;">, &ldquo;Websites&rdquo;; (2) you purchase and use our products and services (&ldquo;Products&rdquo;); (3) you visit one of our physical store locations; (4) you communicate with us in any manner, including by email, direct messaging, telephone, and/or in person; and (4) we interact with certain third parties.&nbsp;</span></p>
      <p><strong><span style="font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;">What Type Of Information Do We Collect From And About You?</span></strong></p>
      <p><span style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;">We may collect the following information from and about you:</span></p>
      <ul>
         <li style="list-style-type:disc;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;">
            <p><strong><span style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;">Basic Identifying Information</span></strong><span style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;">. Information such as your full name, company, e-mail address, phone number, mailing address, account name, username, and other similar identifiers.</span></p>
         </li>
         <li style="list-style-type:disc;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;">
            <p><strong><span style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;">Device Identifier and other Unique Identifiers</span></strong><span style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;">. Information such as your device identifier, internet protocol (IP) address, cookies, beacons, pixel tags, mobile ad identifier, and other unique identifiers.</span></p>
         </li>
         <li style="list-style-type:disc;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;">
            <p><strong><span style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;">Internet or Other Network Activity</span></strong><span style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;">. Information such as your browsing or search history on our Websites, information regarding your interactions with our Websites, email communications, and advertisements.</span></p>
         </li>
         <li style="list-style-type:disc;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;">
            <p><strong><span style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;">Commercial Information</span></strong><span style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;">. Information such as the Websites you have used, the Products you have purchased, and the stores you have visited. &nbsp;</span></p>
         </li>
         <li style="list-style-type:disc;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;">
            <p><strong><span style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;">Audio and Visual Information</span></strong><span style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;">. We may from time to time have recordings of your voice (such as when we record customer service calls for quality assurance) and may have visual records of when you enter our stores via security surveillance footage.</span></p>
         </li>
         <li style="list-style-type:disc;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;">
            <p><strong><span style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;">Inferences</span></strong><span style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;">. Information such as inferences drawn from or created based on the information identified above.</span></p>
         </li>
      </ul>
      <h2><strong><span style="font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;">How Do We Collect Your Information?</span></strong></h2>
      <p><span style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;">We collect your information:</span></p>
      <ul>
         <li style="list-style-type:disc;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;">
            <p><strong><span style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;">Directly From You</span></strong><span style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;">. We collect your information when you provide it directly to us, such as when you make a purchase on our Websites or in our stores, contact us, respond to a survey, RSVP for an event, interact with us in our store, participate in sweepstakes, contests, or other similar campaigns or promotions, apply for a job, or sign-up to receive communications from us.</span></p>
         </li>
         <li style="list-style-type:disc;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;">
            <p><strong><span style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;">Using Online Tracking Technologies and Other Automatic Collection Technologies.</span></strong><span style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;">&nbsp;We collect information from and about you via certain online tracking technologies such as pixels, web beacons, and cookies when you visit our Websites, open or click on emails we send you, or interact with our advertisements. To learn more about these technologies, see Cookies and Similar Online Tracking Technologies below.</span></p>
         </li>
         <li style="list-style-type:disc;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;">
            <p><strong><span style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;">Using In-Store and Offline Technologies</span></strong><span style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;">. We collect information from and about you when we record customer service calls, maintain a transcript of calls for quality assurance purposes, use security cameras in our physical stores for safety, security, and loss prevention purposes, and use other related technologies.</span></p>
