         </li>
      </ul>
      <h2><strong><span style="font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;">Cookies and Similar online Tracking Technologies</span></strong></h2>
      <p><span style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;">We and our third-party partners and service providers use cookies, pixels, web beacons, and similar online tracking technologies to gather information about you when you interact with our Websites, advertisements, and email communications. Some of these technologies help us maintain the security of our Websites, prevent crashes, fix bugs, save your preferences, and assist with basic website functions. We also permit third parties and service providers to use online tracking technologies on our Websites, advertisements, and email communications for analytics and advertising, such as to help manage and display advertisements, tailor advertisements to your interests, send abandoned shopping cart reminders, and for ad measurement purposes.If you are a California resident, some of these technologies may constitute a &ldquo;sale&rdquo; or &ldquo;sharing&rdquo; of your personal information. You can opt-out of these online tracking technologies following our cookie management process.</span></p>
      <h2><strong><span style="font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;">How Do We Use Your Information?</span></strong></h2>
      <p><span style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;">We use your information for a variety of purposes, including:</span></p>
      <p><br></p>
